*Milky Way Extinction*\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 The Milky Way extinction i.e. E(B-V) value of all the supernovae in the training set has been rescaled by 14% as prescribed in Schlafly and Finkbeiner 2011, such that:\
\
	current value = old value * 0.86\
\
This surface should therefore only be used on supernovae that have had their Milky Way extinction scaled to comply with Schlafly and Finkbeiner 2011.\
\
