\f0\b \cf0 *Zero Points*\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 We have updated the zero-points to reflect the changes prescribed by Supercal in Table 5 of https://arxiv.org/abs/1710.00845 and can confirm that all of the supernovae in the training sample used to produce this surface have had the correct offsets applied.  
\f2\i However
\f1\i0 , the SALT2 data contains some extra magnitude systems and instruments for test samples, that may not have had zero-point offsets applied by Supercal.  You can check the files used for your specific sample to see if offsets have been applied or not.\
\
Here is a list of magnitude system/instrument keys that we have applied ZP offsets to (fitmodel.card will point to the datafile for each key):\
\
	
\f2\i (MagSys/B12-AB-off.dat)
\f1\i0 \
	AB_B12/SDSS\
	AB_B12/MEGACAMPSF (for SNLS)\
\
	
\f2\i (MagSys/BD17-jla1.dat)
\f1\i0 \
	VEGA2/KEPLERCAM (for CfA3Kep/CfA4)\
	VEGA2/4SHOOTER2 (for CfA3S)\
	VEGA2/SWOPE2 (for CSP)\
\
	
\f2\i (MagSys/BD17-jla1_CfA1_s18.dat)
\f1\i0 \
	CFA1_S18/STANDARD (for CfA1)\
\
	
\f2\i (MagSys/BD17-jla1_CfA1_s18.dat)
\f1\i0 \
	CFA2_S18/STANDARD (for CfA2)\
\
(Note: as CfA1 and CfA2 use different zero-point offsets for the same instrument, we have created new \'91magnitude systems\'92 in SALT2 for them, so the correct offsets can be applied.  To use the surface on SN from CfA1 or CfA2, change the magnitude system of the SN data to \'91CFA1_S18\'92 or \'91CFA2_S18\'92).\
